snippet: After a year of negotiations with the contractor, the Pentagon said it would pay 4 percent less for each of the 32 radar-evading planes.
abstract: Lockheed Martin announces that it expects to earn percentage profits in the high single digits under new contract to produce another 32 of its high-tech F-35 fighter planes.
lead_paragraph: After a year of negotiations with the contractor, the Pentagon said it would pay 4 percent less for each of the 32 radar-evading planes.

headline.seo: Lockheed’s Profit on F-35 Will Rise With New Pentagon Contract
headline.main: Lockheed Profit on F-35 Jets Will Rise With New Contract
